Quote: Michael Morris of Wellington, says the term "deal to" sounds strange to him as a New Zealand citizen returning after 22 years away. He says he hears New Zealanders but never British people saying "deal to" and much to his surprise has also seen it in print here. He quotes a Lloyd Jones short story saying "... and the intervening coastline looked to have been dealt to with a meat cleaver".... That said, "deal to is accepted by Oxford's <i>Dictionary of NZ English</i> with plenty of citation.
